WEBVTT

1
00:00:13.185 --> 00:00:15.662
I have a two-year-old daughter named Naya
我有一个两岁的女儿，名叫娜娅，

2
00:00:15.686 --> 00:00:21.139
who is under the mistaken impression that this conference is named in honor of her father.
她误认为这个会议的名字是在向他的父亲致敬。

3
00:00:21.163 --> 00:00:22.462
(Laughter)
（笑声）

4
00:00:22.486 --> 00:00:24.622
Who am I to contradict my baby girl?
我哪里敢反驳我的宝贝女儿呢？

5
00:00:25.495 --> 00:00:29.365
As many of you know, there's something about becoming a parent
很多人都有体会，为人父母之后，

6
00:00:29.389 --> 00:00:33.849
that concentrates the mind on long-term problems like climate change.
才会更留心气候变化之类的长期问题。

7
00:00:34.404 --> 00:00:39.447
It was the birth of my daughter that inspired me to launch this climate organization,
是我女儿的出生启发了我去建立这个气候组织，

8
00:00:39.471 --> 00:00:44.675
in order to counteract the excessive polarization of this issue in the United States,
为了对抗美国在这个问题上的过度分化，

9
00:00:44.699 --> 00:00:49.152
and to find a conservative pathway forward.
并找到一个保守的发展路径。

10
00:00:49.970 --> 00:00:54.603
Yes, folks, a Republican climate solution is possible,
是的伙计们，一个共和党气候策略是可能的，

11
00:00:54.627 --> 00:00:55.952
and you know what?
更有甚者，

12
00:00:55.976 --> 00:00:58.308
It may even be better.
可能还是个更好的解决方案。

13
00:00:58.332 --> 00:00:59.943
(Laughter)
（笑声）

14
00:00:59.967 --> 00:01:01.628
Let me try to prove that to you.
我来给大家证明一下。

15
00:01:03.089 --> 00:01:07.663
What we really need is a killer app to climate policy.
我们真正需要的是一个针对气候政策的杀手级应用。

16
00:01:07.687 --> 00:01:12.104
In the technology world, a killer app is an application so transformative
在技术领域，一个杀手级应用是一个变革性的应用，

17
00:01:11.998 --> 00:01:13.551
that it creates its own market,
可以打造属于自己的市场，

18
00:01:13.631 --> 00:01:15.196
like Uber.
比如优步。

19
00:01:15.220 --> 00:01:16.847
In the climate world,
在气候问题的领域中，

20
00:01:16.871 --> 00:01:21.796
a killer app is a new solution so promising
一个杀手级应用是一个颇具前景的新策略，

21
00:01:21.820 --> 00:01:27.252
that it can break through the seemingly insurmountable barriers to progress.
可以打破看似坚不可摧的壁垒来获得突破。

22
00:01:27.276 --> 00:01:30.801
These include the psychological barrier.
这包含了心理上的壁垒。

23
00:01:30.825 --> 00:01:35.972
Climate advocates have long been encouraging their fellow citizens to make short-term sacrifices now
气候倡议者长久以来一直在鼓励身边的市民暂时牺牲短期的利益，

24
00:01:35.996 --> 00:01:38.033
for benefits that accrue to other people
来造福若干年后

25
00:01:37.947 --> 00:01:41.395
in other countries 30 or 40 years in the future.
其他国家的人们。

26
00:01:41.425 --> 00:01:45.728
It just doesn't fly because it runs contrary to basic human nature.
然而效果甚微，毕竟这有悖基本的人性。

27
00:01:46.507 --> 00:01:49.820
Next is the geopolitical barrier.
其次，还有地域政治壁垒。

28
00:01:49.844 --> 00:01:52.112
Under the current rules of global trade,
在当前的国际贸易规则下，

29
00:01:52.136 --> 00:01:57.765
countries have a strong incentive to free ride off the emissions reductions of other nations,
各个国家都有着强烈的意愿去单方面敦促其他国家减少碳排放，

30
00:01:57.789 --> 00:02:00.021
instead of strengthening their own programs.
而并非强化自己国家的相关政策。

31
00:02:00.045 --> 00:02:05.590
This has been the curse of every international climate negotiations, including Paris.
这长期以来都是每一个国际气候谈判的症结所在，包括巴黎协议。

32
00:02:06.243 --> 00:02:09.298
Finally, we have the partisan barrier.
最后，我们还有党派之间的冲突。

33
00:02:09.322 --> 00:02:11.393
Even the most committed countries --
即便是最有决心的几个国家——

34
00:02:11.417 --> 00:02:14.617
Germany, the United Kingdom, Canada --
德国，英国，加拿大——

35
00:02:14.641 --> 00:02:19.362
are nowhere near reducing emissions at the required scale and speed.
也都离合约要求的减排规模和速度存在差距。

36
00:02:19.386 --> 00:02:20.854
Not even close.
而且相差甚远。

37
00:02:20.878 --> 00:02:27.025
And the partisan climate divide is far more acute here in the United States.
而在美国，各党派在气候问题上的分歧更是有过之而无不及。

38
00:02:27.623 --> 00:02:29.729
We are fundamentally stuck,
我们基本是在停滞不前，

39
00:02:29.753 --> 00:02:36.078
and that is why we need a killer app of climate policy to break through each of these barriers.
因此更需要一个气候政策的杀手应用去打破所有这些壁垒。

40
00:02:36.570 --> 00:02:42.238
I'm convinced that the road to climate progress in the United States
我相信气候问题在美国要想取得进展，

41
00:02:42.262 --> 00:02:46.985
runs through the Republican Party and the business community.
需要依靠共和党以及商业界的支持。

42
00:02:47.992 --> 00:02:50.792
So in launching the Climate Leadership Council,
因此我发起了气候领导委员会，

43
00:02:50.852 --> 00:02:55.980
I started by reaching out to a who's who of Republican elder statesmen and business leaders,
最初就尝试着与共和党的政治大佬和商业领袖沟通，

44
00:02:55.944 --> 00:02:59.275
including James Baker and George Schultz,
包括詹姆斯·贝克和乔治·舒兹，

45
00:02:59.405 --> 00:03:03.525
the two most respected Republican elder statesmen in America;
美国最具影响力的两位政界大佬；

46
00:03:03.549 --> 00:03:05.418
Martin Feldstein and Greg Mankiw,
马丁·菲尔德斯坦和格雷格·曼昆，

47
00:03:05.442 --> 00:03:09.084
the two most respected conservative economists in the country;
美国最有威望的两位保守派经济学家；

48
00:03:08.968 --> 00:03:11.125
and Henry Paulson and Rob Walton,
还有亨利·鲍尔森和罗伯·沃顿，

49
00:03:11.225 --> 00:03:14.194
two of the most successful and admired business leaders.
最成功，最受人敬仰的两位商业领袖。

50
00:03:14.218 --> 00:03:19.607
Together, we co-authored "The Conservative Case For Carbon Dividends."
我们共同撰写了《碳红利保守方案》。

51
00:03:19.631 --> 00:03:28.318
This represents the first time that Republican leaders put forth a concrete market-based climate solution.
这标志着共和党领导人第一次合作推动了坚实的基于市场经济的气候策略。

52
00:03:28.342 --> 00:03:29.723
(Applause)
（掌声）

53
00:03:29.747 --> 00:03:30.816
Thank you.
谢谢大家。

54
00:03:30.840 --> 00:03:33.443
(Applause)
（掌声）

55
00:03:33.467 --> 00:03:38.520
We presented our plan at the White House two weeks after President Trump moved in.
特朗普总统搬入白宫两个星期后，我们就在那里对这一计划做了汇报。

56
00:03:39.465 --> 00:03:45.614
Almost every leading editorial board in the country has since endorsed our plan,
全国几乎每一个主流编辑委员会都为我们的计划进行了背书，

57
00:03:45.638 --> 00:03:52.698
and Fortune 100 companies from a wide range of industries are now getting behind it.
而且财富100强中各个领域的企业也都成为了我们坚实的后盾。

58
00:03:52.722 --> 00:03:54.683
So by now you're probably wondering,
那么现在你们可能很好奇，

59
00:03:54.707 --> 00:03:57.109
what exactly is this plan?
这到底是个什么计划呢？

60
00:03:56.283 --> 00:04:01.475
Well, our carbon dividends solution is based on four pillars.
事实上，我们的碳红利策略是基于四个要点。

61
00:04:01.525 --> 00:04:05.435
The first is a gradually rising carbon tax.
第一个就是一个逐渐增收的碳税。

62
00:04:05.459 --> 00:04:07.986
Although capitalism is a wonderful system,
虽然资本主义是个很不错的体系，

63
00:04:07.930 --> 00:04:11.039
like many operating systems, it's prone to bugs,
但就像很多操作系统一样，也容易出错，

64
00:04:11.209 --> 00:04:14.402
which, in this case, are called "market failures."
这种情况通常叫做“市场失调”。

65
00:04:14.426 --> 00:04:21.711
By far the largest is that market prices fail to take social and environmental costs into account.
目前出现的最大问题就是市场价格没有将社会和环境成本考虑在内。

66
00:04:21.735 --> 00:04:27.075
That means every market transaction is based on incorrect information.
这就意味着每次市场交易都是基于错误的信息。

67
00:04:27.099 --> 00:04:31.197
This fundamental bug of capitalism, more than any other single factor,
资本主义这个根本性的缺陷，超越了任何其他单一因素，

68
00:04:31.221 --> 00:04:33.977
is to blame for our climate predicament.
要为我们的气候困境负责。

69
00:04:34.580 --> 00:04:37.891
Now in theory, this should be an easy problem to fix.
理论上，这应该是个易如反掌的问题。

70
00:04:37.915 --> 00:04:44.093
Economists agree that the best solution is to put a price on the carbon content of fossil fuels,
经济学家一致认为最好的解决方案是给化石燃料的碳含量定个价，

71
00:04:44.117 --> 00:04:46.391
otherwise known as a carbon tax.
换句话说就是征碳税。

72
00:04:46.415 --> 00:04:54.221
This would discourage carbon emissions in every single economic transaction, every day of the year.
这样一来就会在每一天的每一项经济交易中抑制碳排放。

73
00:04:54.245 --> 00:04:59.591
However, a carbon tax by itself has proven to be unpopular
然而，事实已经证明碳税本身并不受欢迎，

74
00:04:59.615 --> 00:05:01.283
and a political dead end.
是政策上的死胡同。

75
00:05:01.813 --> 00:05:05.338
The answer is to return all the money raised
而答案应该是把所有缴纳的费用

76
00:05:05.362 --> 00:05:07.654
directly to citizens,
以每月固定红利的形式，

77
00:05:07.678 --> 00:05:11.029
in the form of equal monthly dividends.
直接回馈给老百姓。

78
00:05:11.499 --> 00:05:18.297
This would transform an unpopular carbon tax into a popular and populist solution,
这样一来就可以把不受欢迎的碳税转换成为受欢迎的，大众化的解决方案，

79
00:05:18.321 --> 00:05:23.482
and it would also solve the underlying psychological barrier that we discussed,
同时也能够解决之前谈到过的潜在的心理壁垒，

80
00:05:23.506 --> 00:05:28.183
by giving everyone a concrete benefit in the here and now.
仅仅需要给每个人一个实实在在的，当下的福利。

81
00:05:29.127 --> 00:05:31.416
And these benefits would be significant.
这些福利的影响将是巨大的。

82
00:05:31.440 --> 00:05:35.182
Assuming a carbon tax rate that starts at 40 dollars per ton,
假设碳税率为每吨40美元起，

83
00:05:35.206 --> 00:05:39.884
a family of four would receive 2,000 dollars per year from the get-go.
一个四口之家从征税开始以后就能每年得到2千美元。

84
00:05:40.463 --> 00:05:42.706
According to the US Treasury Department,
根据美国财政部的政策，

85
00:05:43.459 --> 00:05:48.489
the bottom 70 percent of Americans would receive more in dividends
美国底层70%的百姓，相比缴纳日益增长的能源费用，

86
00:05:48.513 --> 00:05:51.804
than they would pay in increased energy prices.
反而将会收到更多的红利。

87
00:05:51.828 --> 00:05:58.821
That means 223 million Americans would win economically
也就是说2亿多的美国人民将会因为解决气候问题

88
00:05:58.845 --> 00:06:00.855
from solving climate change.
而在经济上获益。

89
00:06:01.631 --> 00:06:02.793
And that --
而且——

90
00:06:02.817 --> 00:06:03.872
(Applause)
（掌声）

91
00:06:03.896 --> 00:06:05.446
is revolutionary,
这是革命性的，

92
00:06:05.470 --> 00:06:09.201
and could fundamentally alter climate politics.
也会从根本上改变气候政治现状。

93
00:06:10.598 --> 00:06:13.415
But there's another revolutionary element here.
不过这其中还有另外一个革命性的因素。

94
00:06:13.439 --> 00:06:19.304
The amount of the dividend would grow as the carbon tax rate increases.
红利的数额将会随着碳税率的上涨而增加。

95
00:06:19.328 --> 00:06:21.404
The more we protect our climate,
我们对气候的保护工作做得越好，

96
00:06:21.428 --> 00:06:23.283
the more our citizens benefit.
我们的市民获利就越多。

97
00:06:23.307 --> 00:06:25.529
This creates a positive feedback loop,
这就产生了一个积极的反馈机制，

98
00:06:25.553 --> 00:06:27.083
which is crucial,
这很重要，

99
00:06:27.107 --> 00:06:31.003
because the only way we will reach our long-term emission-reduction goals
因为我们能达到长期减排目标的唯一途径

100
00:06:30.957 --> 00:06:33.783
is if the carbon tax rate goes up every year.
就是碳税率会逐年增长。

101
00:06:34.799 --> 00:06:43.430
The third pillar of our program is eliminating regulations that are no longer needed once a carbon dividends plan is enacted.
第三个关键点是要取消碳红利计划实施后就可以取消各项规章制度。

102
00:06:43.454 --> 00:06:49.883
This is a key selling point to Republicans and business leaders.
这是共和党和商业领袖们一个关键的卖点

103
00:06:50.919 --> 00:06:55.517
So why should we trade climate regulations for a price on carbon?
那么为什么要用碳税来换取代气候保护法规呢？

104
00:06:55.541 --> 00:06:57.319
Well, let me show you.
我来解释一下。

105
00:06:57.996 --> 00:07:02.424
Our plan would achieve nearly twice the emissions reductions
我们的计划将会实现相当于奥巴马时代

106
00:07:02.448 --> 00:07:06.604
of all Obama-era climate regulations combined,
所有气候协议要求的减排量的两倍，

107
00:07:06.628 --> 00:07:14.419
and nearly three times the new baseline after President Trump repeals all of those regulations.
同时也是特朗普总统废除所有规定后设定的新的基准线的三倍。

108
00:07:14.443 --> 00:07:18.206
That assumes a carbon tax starting at 40 dollars per ton,
假设以收每吨40美元的碳税为起点，

109
00:07:18.230 --> 00:07:23.223
which translates into roughly an extra 36 cents per gallon of gas.
那么每加仑汽油会增加36美分的税。

110
00:07:23.882 --> 00:07:26.391
Our plan by itself
我们的计划本身

111
00:07:26.415 --> 00:07:32.290
would meet the high end of America's commitment under the Paris Climate Agreement,
将会达到巴黎气候协议中美国所承诺的上限，

112
00:07:32.314 --> 00:07:33.988
and as you can see,
你们可以看到，

113
00:07:33.972 --> 00:07:36.998
the emissions reductions would continue over time.
减排会随着时间持续下去。

114
00:07:37.521 --> 00:07:46.001
This illustrates the power of a conservative climate solution based on free markets and limited government.
这就证明了一个基于自由市场和有限政府的保守派气候策略的效果是多么显著。

115
00:07:45.995 --> 00:07:52.294
We would end up with less regulation and far less pollution at the same time,
我们要同时实现制度简化和减少污染，

116
00:07:52.344 --> 00:07:56.328
while helping working-class Americans get ahead.
更要帮助美国的劳动人民提高生活水平。

117
00:07:56.352 --> 00:07:59.590
Doesn't that sound like something we could all support?
这难道不是我们都可以支持的吗？

118
00:07:59.614 --> 00:08:02.047
(Applause)
（掌声）

119
00:08:05.723 --> 00:08:12.920
The fourth and final pillar of our program is a new climate domino effect, based on border carbon adjustments.
第四点，也是项目的最后一个基本点，是一个基于边界碳调节的新的气候多米诺效应。

120
00:08:12.944 --> 00:08:15.047
Now that may sound complicated,
这听起来有些复杂，

121
00:08:15.071 --> 00:08:16.936
but it, too, is revolutionary,
但它同样也是革命性的，

122
00:08:16.960 --> 00:08:19.821
because it provides us a whole new strategy
因为它为我们提供了一个能实现

123
00:08:19.845 --> 00:08:22.393
to reach a global price on carbon,
全球碳价统一的新策略，

124
00:08:22.417 --> 00:08:24.284
which is ultimately what we need.
这也是我们的最终目标。

125
00:08:24.308 --> 00:08:26.240
Let me show you an example.
给大家看个例子。

126
00:08:26.264 --> 00:08:29.765
Suppose Country A adopts a carbon dividends plan,
假设A国采纳了一个碳红利计划，

127
00:08:29.789 --> 00:08:31.236
and Country B does not.
但是B国并没有。

128
00:08:31.260 --> 00:08:33.663
Well, to level the playing field
那么为了公平起见，

129
00:08:33.687 --> 00:08:36.922
and protect the competitiveness of its industries,
同时保护本国工业的竞争力，

130
00:08:36.946 --> 00:08:42.707
Country A would tax imports from Country B based on their carbon content.
A国就需要根据B国商品的碳含量对其征收进口关税。

131
00:08:42.731 --> 00:08:44.248
Fair enough.
非常公平。

132
00:08:44.272 --> 00:08:46.416
But here's where it gets really interesting,
不过最耐人寻味的地方在于，

133
00:08:46.440 --> 00:08:52.356
because the money raised at the border would increase the dividends going to the citizens of Country A.
征收的关税将会增加A国公民的碳红利。

134
00:08:52.380 --> 00:08:56.552
Well, how long do you think it would take the public in Country B to realize
那么你们觉得B国需要多长时间才会认识到

135
00:08:56.576 --> 00:08:58.508
that that money should be going to them,
那些钱应该收入自己的口袋，

136
00:08:58.533 --> 00:09:01.522
and to push for a carbon dividends plan in their own land?
需要在自己的国家也推行碳红利计划？

137
00:09:01.546 --> 00:09:03.045
Add a few more countries,
在更多的国家加入之后，

138
00:09:03.069 --> 00:09:06.526
and we get a new climate domino effect.
我们就会制造出一个新的气候多米诺效应。

139
00:09:07.337 --> 00:09:13.275
Once one major country or region adopts carbon dividends with border carbon adjustments,
一旦一个主要国家或者地区采纳了带有边界碳调节的碳红利计划，

140
00:09:13.299 --> 00:09:15.758
other countries are compelled to follow suit.
其他国家就不得不跟进，效仿。

141
00:09:15.782 --> 00:09:18.694
One by one the dominoes fall.
一个接一个，多米诺就这么倒了。

142
00:09:18.718 --> 00:09:21.047
And this domino effect could start anywhere.
而且这个多米诺效应可以始于任何地方。

143
00:09:21.071 --> 00:09:24.481
My preference, strongly, is the United States,
我个人强烈建议，应该从美国开始，

144
00:09:24.505 --> 00:09:27.032
but it could also start in the United Kingdom,
但也可以从英国，

145
00:09:26.926 --> 00:09:29.138
in Germany or another European country,
德国，或者其他欧洲国家开始，

146
00:09:29.288 --> 00:09:30.816
or even in China.
甚至中国。

147
00:09:31.832 --> 00:09:33.842
Let's take China as an example.
拿中国举个例子。

148
00:09:33.866 --> 00:09:38.410
China is committed to reducing greenhouse gas emissions,
中国承诺要减少温室气体排放，

